1.What is cloud computing?
Cloud computing is nothing but on-demand delivery of IT resources over the internet with pay-as-you-go pricing model,
You can access technical resources over the internet such as:

-servers
-storage
-databases
-networking
-AI tools and many more

This is called cloud computing

Ex: Providers into market AWS/Azure/GCP

Or 

Instead of buying physical servers, companies rent IT resources over the internet

-servers
-storage
-databases
-networking
-AI tools and many more

This is called cloud computing

Ex: Providers into market AWS/Azure/GCP

Note: pay-as-you-go (means pay only for what you use)


Simple Real Life Analogy:
———————————
Think of AWS like:
	-Electricity service
	-You don’t build a power plant
	-You just use and pay for what you consume

Same in AWS:
	-No need to buy servers to run your application
	-Pay only for usage

Why AWS is Important?
——————————
-No upfront infrastructure cost
-Scalable (increase or decrease anytime)
-High reliable and secure
-used by companies like (startups, government, largest enterprises, millions of Active users)

